Description: codeREADr is a cloud-based auto-ID and data capture (AIDC) platform.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: The CodeREADr concept started in 2008 as a mobile ticketing project for AT&T to enable them to invite their largest clients to exclusive concerts. We developed a barcode generator to send electronic tickets to the attendees and a barcode scanner app to validate the digital tickets upon entry. At the time we were using AT&T’s recently launched 3G network and their newest smartphone devices as wireless barcode scanners. The project was a huge success.  Over the next few years, we expanded our core technology to apply to event access control, asset tracking, inventory control, shipping & receiving, attendance, facility access control, facility management, security tracking and many other use cases.  We envisioned a future where iOS and Android devices would exceed the scanning performance offered by purpose-built barcode scanners and it has come true. We are now in a position to both improve productivity and lower costs for our customers by moving AIDC to the cloud.  Innovation has been key to our success and we continue to add features to support our loyal customers who rely on us for their mission-critical business processes.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We are proud to show ATLETO to the world. ATLETO was born out of the frustrations felt by our executive team when it came to connecting with others interested in sporting activities. Currently, everyday athletes don’t have an intuitive way to easily connect with and engage in sports and fitness activities with like minded individuals.  We created a sports app to better connect everyday athletes based on interest, skill level and passion for the same activities. Users can discover other athletes of the same skill level by leveraging a ranking system of ability built into the app. By assigning others “knuckles,” users can rate their fellow athletes based on level of sportsmanship and physical capability. This allows users to engage comfortably and without fear of being outmatched. Users can either host or find sporting activities across 40 sports including basketball, cycling, tennis, running and soccer in cities worldwide including launches in Los Angeles, New York and Miami. We are bringing together everyday athletes to connect and grow their network to sport together.    Check it out - we'd love to hear your feedback. For more information visit our website AtletoSports.com and download it for free on iOS.
